com.github.dm.jrt.core.channel

Interface Channel.OutputChannel<OUT>

  • Type Parameters:
    OUT - the output data type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Channel, Iterable<OUT>, Iterator<OUT>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IOChannel<DATA>
    Enclosing interface:
    Channel

    public static interface Channel.OutputChannel<OUT>
extends Channel, Iterator<OUT>, Iterable<OUT>
    Interface defining an output channel, that is the channel used to read the routine invocation output data.

    Note that the delivery order of the output data might not be guaranteed.

Channel.OutputChannel<OUT> afterMax(@NotNull
                                             UnitDuration timeout)

      • all

        @NotNull
List<OUT> all()
        Consumes all the results by waiting for the routine to complete at the maximum for the set timeout.

        Note that this method invocation will block the calling thread until the routine invocation completes or is aborted, or the timeout elapses.

        Returns:
        the list of results.
        Throws:
        ExecutionTimeoutException - if the channel is set to throw an exception when the timeout elapses.
        RoutineException - if the execution has been aborted.
        IllegalStateException - if this channel is already bound to a consumer or another channel.

        OUT nextOrElse(OUT output)
        Consumes the first available result by waiting at the maximum for the set timeout.
        If the timeout elapses and the channel is not configured to throw an exception or abort the invocation, the specified alternative output is returned.

        Note that this method invocation will block the calling thread until a new output is available, the routine invocation completes or is aborted, or the timeout elapses.

        Parameters:
        output - the default output to return.
        Returns:
